rComments: Do not take this class. He is passionate but boring, reading all his lecture notes, speaking WAY too fast, and makes you blind because he turns all the lights off. You will be exhausted by the end of 1.5 hours, and never want to go back. If you could just listen to him, it would be great, but his exams and midterms are based on his lectures.

I loved going to class everyday. He was so passionate about what he was teaching and that was deffinetly reflected in his lectures. I loved every lecture! I have him again this year and cannot wait to go to class again!He covered every aspect of what was being taught and really you had no excuse to fail the class. Awesome Proffessor!

although he is not clear as to what he expects from the class, he is very precise and passionate about Early Modern Europe. i don't know what that guy (below) was saying, but it is the LIGHTEST amount of work you could ever wish for from a history prof! i ask him for help all the time and he is very nice and gets back to e-mails promptly!

He took an extremely interesting topic (early modern Europe) and made his class the bane of my existance. He's unfriendly, rude, boring, and reads all his lectures. His class was a waste of my time, he assigns far too much work for a second year class. Avoid him, you'll thank me later.
